# Obsidian quality gate

Before claiming a task done (code change, fix, or release), run the project quality checks and **do not finish until both are clean: 0 errors and 0 warnings**.

## Required commands

```bash
bun run lint
bun run build
```

`bun run lint` uses official `eslint-plugin-obsidianmd` **`configs.recommended`** with `--max-warnings 0`. Treat any ESLint **warning** as a failure. Fix it; do not leave warnings, suppress casually, or ship with `--quiet`.

Official sources: [obsidianmd/eslint-plugin](https://github.com/obsidianmd/eslint-plugin), [plugin-review.md](https://github.com/obsidianmd/obsidian-releases/blob/master/plugin-review.md).

## What “quality” covers here

- Lint gate = official `recommended` (includes `obsidianmd/no-unsupported-api`)
- No `globalThis` for window/timers — use `window` or `activeWindow` (popout-safe)
- `PluginSettingTab` uses only `getSettingDefinitions()` + `this.update()` (`minAppVersion` ≥ 1.13.0; no `display()`)
- No direct `js-yaml` in `devDependencies` — pin via `overrides` only (`"js-yaml": "4.3.0"`)
- Obsidian API conventions already enforced by the plugin’s eslint rules

## Done criteria

- [ ] `bun run lint` exits 0 with **no warnings**
- [ ] `bun run build` exits 0
- [ ] If the task touched auth/settings/manifest/deps, re-check the items above explicitly

If lint reports warnings you cannot fix without a product decision, stop and ask — do not mark the task complete.
